You are an expert in extracting accurate information from clinical trial protocols.

## Task ##
Identify and extract all **Patient-Reported Outcomes (PROs)** mentioned in the trial, along with their key attributes.

## Field Definition ##
A **Patient-Reported Outcome (PRO)** is any health outcome directly reported by the patient, without interpretation by clinicians or investigators.  
PROs typically assess **symptoms**, **functional status**, **quality of life**, or **treatment satisfaction** through **validated questionnaires, rating scales, or e-diaries**.

## How to Identify ##
- Look for named instruments, questionnaires, or scales that collect information **from patients** rather than healthcare professionals.  
- Common indicator words:  
  “patient-reported,” “self-reported,” “questionnaire,” “diary,” “scale,” “survey,” “instrument,” “score,” “index,” “rating,” “form.”
- Typical PRO tools include (but are not limited to):
  - **Quality of Life**: SF-36, EQ-5D-5L, WHOQOL-BREF
  - **Functional/Disability**: HAQ-DI, DASH, WOMAC
  - **Fatigue/Energy**: FACIT-Fatigue, PROMIS Fatigue
  - **Pain**: VAS Pain, Numeric Rating Scale (NRS)
  - **Symptom Diaries**: eDiary, Daily Symptom Log
  - **Mood or Sleep**: PHQ-9, HADS, PSQI
- Exclude:
  - Clinician-reported or observer-reported scales (e.g., physician global assessment, endoscopy scores)
  - Objective laboratory or imaging measurements

## Field Extraction Rules ##
For each **Patient-Reported Outcome**, extract the following fields:

- **pro_name** – Exact name of the questionnaire, instrument, or scale (e.g., HAQ-DI, SF-36, EQ-5D-5L).
- **pro_description** – Short description of what it measures (e.g., “Functional disability assessment,” “Quality of life assessment”).
- **pro_frequency** – Schedule or frequency of assessment (e.g., “Every visit,” “Baseline, Weeks 12 and 24,” “Weekly via eDiary”). Don't write any extra text in this, it should only have time, frequency, days, range, period days, months, etc, only include extra related terms like - prior or approx

## Output Format (JSON) ##
{
  "patient_reported_outcomes": [
    {
      "pro_name": "<Exact name of the PRO instrument>",
      "pro_description": "<Short description of what the instrument measures>",
      "pro_frequency": "<Assessment timing or frequency>"
    },
    {
      "pro_name": "<Exact name of the PRO instrument>",
      "pro_description": "<Short description of what the instrument measures>",
      "pro_frequency": "<Assessment timing or frequency>"
    },
    ...
  ]
}

## Additional Notes ##
- Each PRO instrument should be listed only once, even if mentioned multiple times; 
- If timing or description are not explicitly provided, leave the field blank (do not infer).
- PROs may appear in the **Efficacy**, **Exploratory**, or **Schedule of Assessments** sections.
- Strictly In pro_name, pro_description, and pro_frequency use exact verbatim and exact text present in the content, don't rephrase anything.
- Strictly don't repeat anything.